\\nI need to inspect the existing metadata support for version 2.8.2, especially since there’s a failure related to a native run. It seems the body gets truncated after the build phase, suggesting a possible run failure due to setup issues. However, I might not have full logs available to diagnose this. I wonder if not taking any action could be the answer? Still, there’s a concrete dependency involved, and it looks like extra Maven dependencies are needed beyond the usual test scaffolding.\\\"}]}\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"advisory_preparation\\\",\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Add hadoop-common for tests: hadoop-yarn-server-common declares hadoop-common as provided, but normal YARN server-common usage and meaningful API coverage rely on Hadoop common classes that are supplied by a Hadoop runtime.\\\",\\n  \\\"deterministic_setup\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"kind\\\": \\\"dependency\\\",\\n      \\\"coordinate\\\": \\\"org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-common:2.9.0\\\",\\n      \\\"scope\\\": \\\"testImplementation\\\",\\n      \\\"reason\\\": \\\"The artifact POM marks hadoop-common as provided, so it is not pulled transitively for tests, while server-common public APIs and typical coverage points use org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration, security annotations/info, HTTP filter containers, and other Hadoop common runtime classes.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"agent_guidance\\\": \\\"No Docker image, environment variable, or system property is required for meaningful unit-style coverage. Prefer in-process coverage of YARN PBImpl records, ResourceTracker/SCMUploader protocol records, security info/filter initialization with a local Configuration, shared-cache utilities, federation policy/store record classes, and web DAO/helper classes. Avoid requiring a live YARN/HDFS cluster, Kerberos KDC, ZooKeeper server, or SQL database unless a later test deliberately adds matching setup.\\\",\\n  \\\"risks\\\": [\\n    \\\"The module has optional/integration-oriented areas involving ZooKeeper, SQL state stores, Kerberos, and Hadoop services; tests that start those paths may need more setup and should be avoided unless explicitly justified.\\\",\\n    \\\"Hadoop 2.9.0 brings an old dependency stack and broad Hadoop runtime surface, so Native Image failures may still come from reachability metadata rather than missing external services.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0ae650a81b4da448016a3e4faf77c08196a030f343ab59bbdf\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"OCA\",\"model\":\"oca/gpt-5.5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":4474,\"output\":1265,\"cacheRead\":26112,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":31851,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1782468513785,\"responseId\":\"resp_0ae650a81b4da448016a3e4fa256848196a769c3bb4e12c08c\"}}\n\nFILE /home/vjovanov/.pi/agent/sessions/--home-vjovanov-c-forge-forge2-graalvm-reachability-metadata-forge-local_repositories-forge_worktrees-8597-dc22c474--/2026-06-26T10-26-54-902Z_019f0377-dd36-772d-a1c6-c2645bfd8d5c.jsonl\n{\"type\":\"session\",\"version\":3,\"id\":\"019f0377-dd36-772d-a1c6-c2645bfd8d5c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-26T10:26:54.902Z\",\"cwd\":\"/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/8597-dc22c474\"}\n{\"type\":\"model_change\",\"id\":\"060670cc\",\"parentId\":null,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-26T10:26:54.956Z\",\"provider\":\"OCA\",\"modelId\":\"oca/gpt-5.5\"}\n{\"type\":\"thinking_level_change\",\"id\":\"97b8a3cb\",\"parentId\":\"060670cc\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-26T10:26:54.956Z\",\"thinkingLevel\":\"medium\"}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"f0fa6955\",\"parentId\":\"97b8a3cb\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-26T10:26:54.962Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"You are preparing a Forge workflow for a library issue. Decide whether the library needs setup beyond the normal generated test scaffold before meaningful coverage is reachable.\\n\\nResearch the library yourself to make this decision. Investigate the resolved artifact and its dependencies, how the library is normally used, and its documentation. The JSON context below is only a starting point, not the limit of what you may consider. Do not modify the repository or apply any setup yourself — return only the decision. Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\\n\\nThe setup can be one of three things: an extra Maven dependency, a Docker image the tests need, or an environment/system property the generated tests must set. Represent dependencies and Docker images as `deterministic_setup` entries the driver can apply before generation:\\n  - {\\\"kind\\\": \\\"dependency\\\", \\\"coordinate\\\": \\\"group:artifact:version\\\", \\\"scope\\\": \\\"testImplementation\\\", \\\"reason\\\": \\\"...\\\"}\\n  - {\\\"kind\\\": \\\"docker_image\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"name:tag\\\", \\\"slug\\\": \\\"short-slug\\\", \\\"reason\\\": \\\"...\\\"}\\nPut environment variables, system properties, and other test-code setup in `agent_guidance`. Do not restate deterministic entries as guidance.\\n\\nReturn a single JSON object with this shape:\\n{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"no_action\\\" | \\\"advisory_preparation\\\",\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"short reason\\\",\\n  \\\"deterministic_setup\\\": [ ... dependency or docker_image entries, if any ... ],\\n  \\\"agent_guidance\\\": \\\"environment/system property/test setup guidance, if any\\\",\\n  \\\"risks\\\": [\\\"risk notes, if any\\\"]\\n}\\n\\nChoose no_action unless your research finds concrete evidence that extra setup is needed.\\n\\nContext (starting point):\\n{\\n  \\\"issue\\\": {\\n    \\\"number\\\": 8597,\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"[Automation] native-image run fails for org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-yarn-server-common:2.9.0\\\",\\n    \\\"label\\\": \\\"fails-native-image-run\\\",\\n    \\\"body\\