 evidence that an extra setup is needed.\\\"}]}\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"advisory_preparation\\\",\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"The artifact declares org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-common as a provided dependency, and its public/server-common APIs directly reference Hadoop common types such as Configuration, SecurityInfo, KerberosInfo, and FilterContainer. A generated test scaffold that only depends on hadoop-yarn-server-common will not reliably reach meaningful coverage.\\\",\\n  \\\"deterministic_setup\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"kind\\\": \\\"dependency\\\",\\n      \\\"coordinate\\\": \\\"org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-common:2.9.0\\\",\\n      \\\"scope\\\": \\\"testImplementation\\\",\\n      \\\"reason\\\": \\\"hadoop-yarn-server-common 2.9.0 declares hadoop-common with provided scope, but meaningful tests for YARN server-common records, security info, filter initialization, and shared utilities need Hadoop common classes on the test/runtime classpath.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"agent_guidance\\\": \\\"No required Docker image, environment variable, or system property was found. Prefer in-process coverage of PBImpl record classes, BuilderUtils/SharedCacheUtil-style utilities, security/filter initializer classes, and web/DAO helpers. Use Configuration(false) for configuration-driven APIs to avoid loading site files, and avoid starting real ResourceManager/NodeManager/shared-cache services unless the test explicitly owns all temporary directories.\\\",\\n  \\\"risks\\\": [\\n    \\\"This is an internal Hadoop YARN server module with many service-backed classes; tests that try to start full YARN services may require filesystem, Kerberos, database, or ZooKeeper setup that is unnecessary for meaningful metadata coverage.\\\",\\n    \\\"The existing 2.8.2 scaffold already adds hadoop-common explicitly, which is strong evidence that the provided dependency remains needed for the 2.9.0 update.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\