isory preparation**\\\\n\\\\nI need to remember that I shouldn't restate deterministic entries. If there's no specific environment or system property required, the agent guidance can just be empty. It might be helpful to mention that no required environment variables or system properties were found. Still, it could be beneficial to suggest that tests should create Configuration(false) as guidance. I'll choose no action unless there's some concrete evidence that an extra setup is needed.\\\"}]}\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"advisory_preparation\\\",\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"The artifact declares org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-common as a provided dependency, and its public/server-common APIs directly reference Hadoop common types such as Configuration, SecurityInfo, KerberosInfo, and FilterContainer. A generated test scaffold that only depends on hadoop-yarn-server-common will not reliably reach meaningful coverage.\\\",\\n  \\\"deterministic_setup\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"kind\\\": \\\"dependency\\\",\\n      \\\"coordinate\\\": \\\"org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-common:2.9.0\\\",\\n      \\\"scope\\\": \\\"testImplementation\\\",\\n      \\\"reason\\\": \\\"hadoop-yarn-server-common 2.9.0 declares hadoop-common with provided scope, but meaningful tests for YARN server-common records, security info, filter initialization, and shared utilities need Hadoop common classes on the test/runtime classpath.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"agent_guidance\\\": \\\"No required Docker image, environment variable, or system property was found. Prefer in-process coverage of PBImpl record classes, BuilderUtils/SharedCacheUtil-style utilities, security/filter initializer classes, and web/DAO helpers. Use Configuration(false) for configuration-driven APIs to avoid loading site files, and avoid starting real ResourceManager/NodeManager/shared-cache services unless the test explicitly owns all temporary directories.\\\",\\n  \\\"risks\\\": [\\n    \\\"This is an internal Hadoop YARN server module with many service-backed classes; tests that try to start full YARN services may require filesystem, Kerberos, database, or ZooKeeper setup that is unnecessary for meaningful metadata coverage.\\\",\\n    \\\"The existing 2.8.2 scaffold already adds hadoop-common explicitly, which is strong evidence that the provided dependency remains needed for the 2.9.0 update.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_03281293dfaee1de016a3e54288f288195b3a56fed8eb649bd\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"OCA\",\"model\":\"oca/gpt-5.5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":952,\"output\":882,\"cacheRead\":23040,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":24874,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1782469657095,\"responseId\":\"resp_03281293dfaee1de016a3e541989188195b191efd1f08f5faa\"}}\n/home/vjovanov/.pi/agent/sessions/--home-vjovanov-c-forge-forge2-graalvm-reachability-metadata-forge-local_repositories-forge_worktrees-8597-18f1886d--/2026-06-26T10-07-14-898Z_019f0365-dbd2-749c-af85-9b65cd13483b.jsonl:4:{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"92e5af8a\",\"parentId\":\"f7bfa0ce\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-26T10:07:14.956Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"You are preparing a Forge workflow for a library issue. Decide whether the library needs setup beyond the normal generated test scaffold before meaningful coverage is reachable.\\n\\nResearch the library yourself to make this decision. Investigate the resolved artifact and its dependencies, how the library is normally used, and its documentation. The JSON context below is only a starting point, not the limit of what you may consider. Do not modify the repository or apply any setup yourself — return only the decision. Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\\n\\nThe setup can be one of three things: an extra Maven dep