ecommend the hadoop-common dependency. That might cause duplication, so the driver could check for existing dependencies first. I might need to dig into Forge docs for more details, but the user didn't specifically request that.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Reviewing Maven dependencies**\\\\n\\\\nI'm checking if the Maven runtime dependencies include hadoop-common, using the POM information. It looks like hadoop-common is provided in the target POM but isn't transitively resolved. My JSON summary needs to be valid and concise. I need to include a deterministic setup for hadoop-common due to its relationships with various APIs. \\\\n\\\\nShould I also consider hadoop-auth? It seems like hadoop-common depends on that, but it might already be included. Lastly, I need to look into the relevance of the hadoop-yarn-common test jar and potential Docker images for the target dependencies.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering SQL storage options**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking that the SQL store could definitely utilize in-memory HSQLDB if I add the hsqldb dependency. But for meaningful coverage, it seems like I really need SQL. Given that, I’m concluding that using Docker isn’t necessary in this scenario. It sounds like an in-memory database can be helpful, but I'd have to ensure the tests and coverage are comprehensive without overcomplicating things with additional setups.\\\"}]}\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"action\\\": \\\"advisory_preparation\\\",\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"The artifact’s normal YARN server APIs depend on Hadoop Common classes that are declared as Maven provided scope, so a target-only scaffold is likely blocked before meaningful coverage.\\\",\\n  \\\"deterministic_setup\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"kind\\\": \\\"dependency\\\",\\n      \\\"coordinate\\\": \\\"org.apache.hadoop:hadoop-common:2.9.0\\\",\\n      \\\"scope\\\": \\\"testImplementation\\\",\\n      \\\"reason\\\": \\\"hadoop-yarn-server-common:2.9.0 declares hadoop-common as provided, but its public and implementation APIs reference org.apache.hadoop.conf.Configuration, security token/protobuf classes, RPC annotations, and HTTP filter interfaces needed for realistic YARN server-common coverage.\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"agent_guidance\\\": \\\"No Docker service appears necessary for meaningful tests. Prefer in-process coverage of YARN PB records, BuilderUtils, security/filter initialization with Configuration(false), shared-cache utilities, and the in-memory federation store/policy classes. Avoid SQLFederationStateStore and ZookeeperFederationStateStore unless the test explicitly configures embedded/test infrastructure.\\\",\\n  \\\"risks\\\": [\\n    \\\"If the workflow copies the existing 2.8.2 test scaffold, this dependency may already be present and should not be duplicated.\\\",\\n    \\\"Exercising SQL or ZooKeeper federation stores would require additional test infrastructure, but those paths are not necessary for baseline meaningful coverage.\\\"\\n  ]\\n}\",\"textSignature\":\"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0570a188c4e4e5cf016a3e4f0249a08195a69fe7cea8248b4e\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"OCA\",\"model\":\"oca/gpt-5.5\",\"usage\":{\"input\":3073,\"output\":1335,\"cacheRead\":30720,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":35128,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1782468330851,\"responseId\":\"resp_0570a188c4e4e5cf016a3e4eeb55f481958057e3fa08ec3208\"}}\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
